article.headline: Maine 65, Columbia 59
article.story: NEW YORK -- Sean McNally had 16 points, seven rebounds and three steals and Maine rallied to defeat Columbia 65-59 on Wednesday night. The Black Bears (6-5), who shot 6-for-18 from the floor in the first half, trailed 33-24 at halftime. Maine then opened the second half with a 12-2 run to pull ahead 36-35 with 16:04 left. The Lions (5-6) hit five straight free throws to take a 40-38 lead, but Maine answered with a Murphy Burnatowski 3-pointer with 13:17 left and never trailed again. Columbia was 5-for-23 from the field in the second half. With the Black Bears up 61-54, Niko Scott scored five straight points to cut the margin to 61-59 with 42 seconds left. Maine made 4 of 6 free throws to seal the win. Terrance Mitchell added 14 points for Maine. Scott scored 16 points to lead Columbia, which was 5-for-9 from long range in the first half, but only 1-for-6 in the second.
